    "type": "T12",
    "typeName": "情景回应",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U04",
    "unitTheme": "Describing Routes and Finding Entrances",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "prepositions of movement",
      "directions",
      "entrances",
      "routes"
    ],
    "scenario": "你在乡间徒步，遇到一位游客询问如何到达东边的入口。请用英语告诉他路线：沿着河岸走，经过一个河弯，然后一直走向东入口。",
    "options": [
      "Go across the river bank, through the bend, and upon the eastern entrance.",
      "Go along the river bank, past the bend, and towards the eastern entrance.",
      "Go along the river bank, over the bend, and into the eastern entrance."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 1,
    "pragmaticsNote": "指路时，描述沿着路线（along）行经某点（past）并朝向目的地（towards）是常见自然的表达。选项A准确使用了这三个介词。选项B中'across'表示从一端到另一端，不适合描述沿河岸行走；'through the bend'也不符合习惯，弯道不能穿过；'upon'通常不与'entrance'搭配。选项C中'over the bend'表示越过弯道，但路线是沿着河岸，不需要越过；'into the entrance'可以表示进入入口，但句子结构不如'towards'自然地表示方向。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U04-S02"
  },
