  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U08-S05-005",
    "type": "T07",
    "typeName": "Translation Choice",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U08",
    "unitTheme": "Public Decisions, Opinions, and Debate",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "noun clause",
      "whether",
      "that",
      "public debate",
      "vocabulary"
    ],
    "sourceText": "尽管官方发布了公告，要求民众遵守新规定，许多人仍怀疑该决定是否有效，并拒绝接受这一说法。",
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "options": [
      "Although the authority announced the new rule, many people still doubt that the decision is effective and accept the claim.",
      "Despite the authority's announcement that requires the public to follow the new rule, many still doubt the decision will be effective and reject the claim.",
      "Despite the authority's announcement requiring the public to follow the new rule, many still doubt whether the decision will be effective and reject the claim.",
      "Though the authority announced the new rule, many still believe whether the decision will be effective and reject the claim."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 2,
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U08-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U08-S05-006",
    "type": "T08",
    "typeName": "听力选择",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U08",
    "unitTheme": "Public Decisions, Opinions, and Debate",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "noun-clauses",
      "whether-that",
      "public-debate",
      "authority",
      "listening"
    ],
    "audioText": "The school authority announced a new rule requiring all students to wear ID badges at all times. Some students doubt whether this will be effective for security. Others believe that it will help identify visitors. However, a few reject the idea because they think it violates privacy. Despite the debate, the principal claims that the decision is final.",
    "question": "根据听力内容，校长对新规定的态度是什么？",
    "options": [
      "校长认为新规定无效，应该取消",
      "校长怀疑新规定是否有效",
      "校长声称这个决定是最终的"
    ],
    "answerIdx": 2,
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U08-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U08-S05-007",
    "type": "T10",
    "typeName": "翻译输入",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U08",
    "unitTheme": "Public Decisions, Opinions, and Debate",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "noun clause",
      "whether",
      "doubt",
      "public policy"
    ],
    "sourceText": "人们怀疑当局是否会要求执行新规定。",
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "acceptedAnswers": [
      "People doubt whether the authority will require the new regulation to be enforced.",
      "People doubt whether the authorities will require enforcement of the new regulation.",
      "People doubt if the authority will require the new regulation."
    ],
    "hint": "提示：使用 whether 引导的名词性从句表达 doubt（怀疑），结构为 doubt whether + 从句。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U08-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U08-S05-008",
    "type": "T12",
    "typeName": "情景回应",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U08",
    "unitTheme": "Public Decisions, Opinions, and Debate",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "noun-clauses",
      "whether",
      "that",
      "public-debate",
      "modal-verbs"
    ],
    "scenario": "班级正在辩论校方最新发布的“取消期中考试”的通告。同学甲认为：“校方不应该在未征求意见的情况下就做决定。” 你想表达“大家怀疑这个决定是否真能减轻压力”，最地道的回应是：",
    "options": [
      "People doubt whether this decision will actually reduce stress.",
      "People doubt that this decision will actually reduce stress.",
      "People doubt the decision whether reduces stress."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 0,
    "pragmaticsNote": "在表达“怀疑/不确定某事是否会发生”时，doubt whether 引导的名词性从句最准确；doubt that 通常表示“认为……不太可能”，语义偏向否定；选项 C 语法结构错误。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U08-S05"
  },
