      "Nuclear waste is slightly dangerous to the atmosphere, and coal resources are rarely consumed, causing a significant rise in global heating risk.",
      "Nuclear waste is highly dangerous to the atmosphere, and coal resources are rarely consumed, causing a fairly small rise in global heating risk.",
      "Nuclear waste is fairly dangerous to the atmosphere, and coal resources are regularly consumed, causing a slight rise in global heating risk."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 0,
