  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U09-S05-004",
    "type": "T07",
    "typeName": "Translation Choice",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U09",
    "unitTheme": "Natural Events and Process Explanations",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "sequencing",
      "present perfect passive",
      "natural events",
      "vocabulary"
    ],
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "sourceText": "首先，地震发生时，地表层的压力突然释放，导致岩层移动；然后，洪水频繁冲刷河床，水流速度高度加快；最后，飓风已被记录为造成严重破坏的自然灾害。",
    "options": [
      "First, an earthquake occurs and the pressure in the surface layer is released suddenly, moving rock layers; then, floods rarely wash the riverbed, and the water flow speed increased slightly; finally, hurricanes were recorded as natural disasters causing severe damage.",
      "Initially, an earthquake occurs, releasing pressure on the surface layer and moving rock layers; after that, floods frequently erode the riverbed, and the water flow speed increases highly; lastly, hurricanes have been recorded as natural disasters that cause severe damage.",
      "First, when an earthquake occurs, the sudden release of pressure in the surface layer causes rock layers to move; then, floods frequently erode the riverbed, and the water flow speed has been measured to increase highly; finally, hurricanes have been recorded as natural disasters that have been caused severe damage.",
      "First, when an earthquake occurs, the sudden release of pressure in the surface layer causes the rock layers to move; then, floods frequently erode the riverbed, and the water flow speed has been measured as highly increased; finally, hurricanes have been recorded as natural disasters that have caused severe damage."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 3,
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U09-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U09-S05-005",
    "type": "T08",
    "typeName": "听力选择",
    "language": "en",
