  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U09-S05-007",
    "type": "T10",
    "typeName": "翻译输入",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U09",
    "unitTheme": "Natural Events and Process Explanations",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "sequencing",
      "present perfect passive",
      "natural disasters",
      "vocabulary: earthquake, flood, hurricane, occur, flow, layer, surface, pressure, force, sudden, frequently, rarely, slightly, highly"
    ],
    "sourceText": "首先，压力在岩层深处积聚。然后，地震突然发生。之后，地表变形已被测量。最后，破坏力度已被记录。",
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "acceptedAnswers": [
      "First, pressure builds up deep in rock layers. Then, an earthquake occurs suddenly. After that, surface deformation has been measured. Finally, the destructive force has been recorded.",
      "First, pressure accumulates deep in the rock layers. Then, an earthquake happens suddenly. After that, the surface deformation has been measured. Finally, the force of destruction has been recorded.",
      "First, pressure builds in the rock layers. Then, an earthquake strikes suddenly. After that, surface changes have been measured. Finally, the extent of damage has been recorded."
    ],
    "hint": "请使用 first, then, after that, finally 连接句子，并对‘已被测量’和‘已被记录’使用现在完成时被动语态 (has/have been + 过去分词)。注意词汇：pressure, layer, earthquake, sudden, occur, surface, measure, record, force。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U09-S05"
  },
