      "present perfect passive",
      "natural events",
      "adverbs of frequency"
    ],
    "scenario": "你正在向同学解释地震是如何发生的，要求用 first, then, after that, finally 描述过程，并用 has been caused, has been measured 等被动语态说明已记录的变化，同时用 frequently, slightly 等副词表示频率和程度。请选择最合适的回应。",
    "options": [
      "The earthquake happens because plates move. It is measured by scientists. It rarely happens here and is slightly strong.",
      "First, tectonic plates build up pressure. Then, the pressure is released suddenly, causing an earthquake. After that, the seismic waves have been measured by seismographs. Finally, the damage has been recorded in reports. Earthquakes frequently occur in this region, and the shaking is usually highly intense.",
      "First, the ground shakes. Then, the flood comes. After that, the hurricane arrives. Finally, everything is destroyed. It has been caused by nature."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 1,
    "pragmaticsNote": "Uses proper sequencing words (first, then, after that, finally), present perfect passive (has been measured, has been recorded), and adverbs of frequency/degree (frequently, highly).",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U09-S05"
  },
