      "esential",
      "essencial",
      "essentail"
    ],
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U10-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U10-S05-006",
    "type": "T11",
    "typeName": "语音跟读",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U10",
    "unitTheme": "Integrated Communication on Public Issues",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "public speaking",
      "youth responsibility",
      "confidence",
      "complex sentences"
    ],
    "audioText": "Youth should be confident whenever they express opinions.",
    "scoringDimensions": [
      "发音",
      "流利度",
      "完整度"
    ],
    "difficultyNotes": "包含条件状语从句 whenever，词汇涉及青年责任与公共表达，语速中等，适合 B1 学习者跟读练习语调与重音。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U10-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U10-S05-007",
    "type": "T10",
    "typeName": "翻译输入",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U10",
    "unitTheme": "Integrated Communication on Public Issues",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "translation",
      "complex sentences",
      "conditionals",
      "modal verbs",
      "vocabulary: youth awareness"
    ],
    "sourceText": "青年人有必要意识到，无论遇到什么挑战，除非他们未做好准备，否则都应努力参与社会事务，因为这对有效解决问题至关重要。",
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "acceptedAnswers": [
      "It is essential for young people to be aware that, whatever challenges they face, they should make an effort to participate in public affairs unless they are unprepared, because this is crucial for effective solutions.",
      "Young people need to realize that, whatever difficulties they encounter, they ought to strive to engage in social issues unless they are not ready, as this is vital for effective problem-solving."
    ],
    "hint": "注意使用 whatever 引导的让步状语从句、unless 引导的条件状语从句、it is essential that... 结构以及情态动词表达建议/义务。",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U10-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U10-S05-008",
    "type": "T07",
    "typeName": "翻译选择",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U10",
    "unitTheme": "Integrated Communication on Public Issues",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "grammar-review",
      "public-issues",
      "complex-sentences",
      "conditionals",
      "modal-verbs"
    ],
    "sourceText": "青年人必须意识到，除非他们准备好并付出努力，否则无论何时参与公共讨论，他们都无法有效且自信地表达观点。",
    "sourceLang": "zh",
    "options": [
      "Young people must realize that unless they are prepared and make an effort, they will not be able to express their views effectively and confidently whatever they participate in public discussions.",
      "Young people must realize that unless they are prepared and make an effort, they will not be able to express their views effectively and confidently whenever they participate in public discussions.",
      "Young people must realize that if they are prepared and make an effort, they will be able to express their views effectively and confidently whenever they participate in public discussions.",
      "Young people must realize that unless they are prepared and make an effort, they will be able to express their views effectively and confidently whenever they participate in public discussions."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 1,
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U10-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U10-S05-009",
    "type": "T12",
    "typeName": "情景回应",
    "language": "en",
    "cefr": "B1",
    "unit": "U10",
    "unitTheme": "Integrated Communication on Public Issues",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "tags": [
      "conditionals",
      "modal verbs",
      "concessive clauses",
      "public issues",
      "vocabulary: unless, whether, whatever"
    ],
    "scenario": "你们正在为“青年社会责任”小组展示做准备。组员A说：“我认为我们应该强调，只有当青年感觉到自己的声音被听见时，他们才会参与。” 你想表示赞同，并补充指出：除非有关部门给予鼓励，否则青年很难确信他们的付出会有成效，无论议题是什么。你会怎么说？",
    "options": [
      "Exactly. Unless authorities encourage them, young people won't be confident whether their efforts lead to achievements, whatever the issue.",
      "Okay. Youth is essential. We should just tell them whatever they want to hear.",
      "Right. If they aren't aware, they won't join unless we do all the preparation for them."
    ],
    "answerIdx": 0,
    "pragmaticsNote": "Option A correctly uses 'unless' for a negative condition, 'whether' for an indirect question, and 'whatever' for a concessive clause, maintaining a formal, collaborative tone suitable for a presentation prep. Option B incorrectly shifts agency to the speakers ('we do all preparation'). Option C suggests manipulation ('tell them whatever they want to hear'), which is inappropriate for civic discourse.",
    "pairId": "pair_1782569237717",
    "sectionId": "pair_1782569237717/U10-S05"
  },
  {
    "id": "pair_1782569237717-B1-U10-S05-010",
